text: The first movie was funny, interesting and had quite a few sexy and sensual scenes.  But the second movie (I just watched it) is one long, ultra silly, loud (constantly flat and shallow jokes) assault. It lost all the things that made the first movie cool.  Where the first movie exaggerated quite a bit, but still stayed somewhat believable (in a fictional sense) the second movie is completly over the top; uninspriring, boring and just annoying. I found myself getting distracted by all kinds of things while watching. At some point completly losing interest in the movie and starting to heavily yawn.  Bad choice for a script, bad dialogues, wasted humor (which isnt funny) and a waste of hot women and attractive men.  It is either a completly differend director (or is it? too lazy to check) or they just utterly failed this time around.  I'd give the first movie a 6 out of 10 and the second a 3 out of 10.  Not worth spending money or time on if you liked the first movie. Vastly inferior.  But that is only my opinion. If you're critical....check it out yourself.
